reviewText: who wouldn't be interested, G.G. Liddey one of history's greatest  villians!

A fascinating debate on the ethics of being a "stool pigeon". WFB is clearly unsettled by Liddy, which makes sense because WFB was close friends with Whitaker Chambers,  the Soviet Spy turned Conservative writer.

Honest, truthful discussions, Intelligent, and uses more than one syllable words! it was great then. It is a wonderful surprise now!
Watch a show you will wish there was more of now.
A ethics discussion about breaking the law. Additional discussion about jail hierarchy. Nothing about Nixon or the presidency. Classic Buckley.

These shows are amazing! You can watch HISTORY as it was actually unfolding. I didn't know G. Gordon Liddy was given 20 years for refusing to "snitch"  about Watergate. The sentence was finally reduced, but only after an outcry from all factions that it was excessive punishment We get to hear a defense of his position on this show.
